# Build & Testing Overview

## Build System
The project uses [vite.config.js](mdc:vite.config.js) to bundle and serve assets.  Notable points:

* `@vitejs/plugin-basic-ssl` enables local HTTPS.
* `build.outDir` is `dist`, and the directory is emptied on each build.
* `rollupOptions.input` lists multiple HTML entry points so they are compiled alongside the main `index.html`:
  - **Main pages**: [index.html](mdc:index.html), [app.html](mdc:app.html)
  - **Test pages** found under the *tests* directory (see below).
* During development `vite dev` opens `/index.html` automatically thanks to `server.open`.

## Tests Linked in the Build
All demo and regression pages live in the [tests](mdc:tests) folder.  Each HTML file under this directory is added as a separate Rollup input in `vite.config.js`, allowing you to open them directly while the dev server is running.

When new test pages are created, simply drop the HTML file in `tests/` and register it in the `rollupOptions.input` map.  No further configuration is needed.

## Components Folder
Reusable scene primitives live in [src/components](mdc:src/components):

* [VectorVisualization.js](mdc:src/components/VectorVisualization.js) — converts an array of numbers into a vertical stack of cubes/ellipses, with utility helpers `layerNormalize` and disposal logic.
* [WeightMatrixVisualization.js](mdc:src/components/WeightMatrixVisualization.js) — parametric trapezoidal prism with vertical slits that vectors pass through.  Exposes `updateGeometry` for live-GUI tweaks.

These components purposefully avoid direct scene references so they can be embedded in multiple animations/tests.

## Forthcoming GPT Extraction Layer
A nascent Python package under [`gpt_extraction`](mdc:gpt_extraction) will provide utilities to pull hidden states and other internals from a GPT forward pass.  Early stubs include:

* [utils.py](mdc:gpt_extraction/utils.py)
* [model.py](mdc:gpt_extraction/model.py)
* [bpe.py](mdc:gpt_extraction/bpe.py)

Expect tighter integration between the Three.js visualizer and these extraction scripts once the Python APIs solidify.

